<title>Landscape Restoration, Minor</title>


<text>
<![CDATA[  

  
]]>
</text>
<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p>This minor is of particular interest to students majoring in Wildlife, Fish, &amp; Conservation Biology, Environmental Science &amp; Management, Landscape Architecture, Biological Sciences, Evolution &amp; Ecology, Plant Biology, and Sustainable Environmental Design.</p>
<p><span class="sc_courseinline"><span class="code_bubble" data-code-bubble="BIS 002C">BIS 002C</span></span> or <span class="sc_courseinline"><span class="code_bubble" data-code-bubble="PLS 002">PLS 002</span></span> is a prerequisite to most courses in the minor.</p>

<p>The minor is sponsored by the <a href="/departments-programs-degrees/plant-sciences/plant-science-bs/" target="_blank">Department of Plant Sciences</a>.</p>
<h2>Minor Advisor</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.plantsciences.ucdavis.edu/academics/undergraduate/programs" target="_blank">Plant Sciences Advising</a>; <a href="mailto:plsadvising@ucdavis.edu">plsadvising@ucdavis.edu</a></p>
]]>
</informationtext>
<requirementstext name="Requirements">
<![CDATA[
<p>Successful completion of the minor requires the following:</p>
<ul>
	<li>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</li>
	<li>Minimum overall GPA of 2.000.</li>
	<li>No more than one course can be counted towards both the student’s major and the minor.</li>
</ul>
